ent is an act of unbelief, and between people it is illicit.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 9100 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0635\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":42699,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/07\/despair-major-sin\/","url_meta":{"origin":3501,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Kaba\u2019ir: Despairing of Allah\u2019s mercy a major sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 7, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what are the major sins?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him said, \u201cIdolatry with Allah, losing hope in relief from Allah, and despair in the mercy of Allah.\u201d Source: Kashf al-Asta\u0304r 106 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37275,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/10\/31\/shirk-hope-fear\/","url_meta":{"origin":3501,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Kaba\u2019ir: Idolatry, losing hope, not fearing Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 31, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: A man came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cWhat are the major sins?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cTo associate partners with Allah, to despair of relief from Allah, and to feel safe from the plan of Allah. These are\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":9938,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/11\/24\/iman-yaman-kufr-mashriq\/","url_meta":{"origin":3501,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Yemen: Faith is Yemeni, peace among sheep","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFaith is from Yemen and unbelief is from the east. Tranquility is found among people who tend to sheep. Pride and showing off are found among the uncivil owners of horses and camels.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37511,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/14\/angels-say-three\/","url_meta":{"origin":3501,"position":5},"title":"Ibn Abbas on Akhirah: Angels say one of three things upon death","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 14, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Barbahari reported: Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cKnow that there are three tidings at the time of death. It will be said: Receive glad tings of the pleasure of Allah, O beloved of Allah, and Paradise! And it will be said: Receive tidings of the anger\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3501","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=3501"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3501\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=3501"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=3501"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=3501"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}